    "body": "NACK this removes doxygen comments, and distances comments from their relevant context.\r\n\r\nYou might want to turn your attention to changes that provide test-confirmable improvements, which are more likely to have concrete benefits. The contributing guide discourages refactoring changes for new developers for that reason, see #11276:\r\n\r\n> Pull requests that refactor the code should not be made by new contributors. It requires a certain level of experience to know where the code belongs to and to understand the full ramification (including rebase effort of open pull requests).\r\nhttps://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#refactoring",
